# Firebase Backend Setup Plan

This plan outlines the steps to correctly configure Firestore and Firebase Storage for the "Roze" app.

## Security Rules

We need to ensure that users can only access their own data.

### Firestore Rules
These rules silo data by `userId` to match the current [FirestoreService](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/firestore_service.dart#5-26) implementation.

```javascript
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /journals/{userId} {
      // Allow user to read/write their own journal document
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
      
      match /entries/{dateKey} {
        // Allow user to read/write their own entries
        allow read, write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Storage Rules
These rules protect photos and videos uploaded by users.

```javascript
rules_version = '2';
service firebase.storage {
  match /b/{bucket}/o {
    match /images/{userId}/{allPaths=**} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }
    match /videos/{userId}/{allPaths=**} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }
  }
}
```

## Proposed Changes

### [Firebase Configuration]

#### [NEW] [firebase_options.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/firebase_options.dart)
This file will be generated via `flutterfire configure` to support Web, Android, and iOS from a single project.

#### [MODIFY] [main.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/main.dart)
Update the initialization to use the generated options.

```dart
await Firebase.initializeApp(
  options: DefaultFirebaseOptions.currentPlatform,
);
```

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  **Firebase Console**: I will guide the user through the Firebase Console to apply the security rules.
2.  **Flutter App**: Run the app and attempt to save an entry.
3.  **Verify Firestore**: Check the Firebase Console to see if the entry appears under the correct `userId`.
4.  **Verify Storage**: Check the Firebase Storage bucket for uploaded media.
